      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a 2011 BMW M3 Coupe (E92) featuring the legendary S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving power unit utilizes individual throttle bodies and an 8,400 RPM redline, delivering linear power through a lightning-fast 7-speed M-DCT dual-clutch transmission. The chassis remains taut with Electronic Damper Control (EDC) providing adaptable damping rates, while the variable M differential lock ensures optimal traction out of corners. Maintenance is up to date, including a proactive rod bearing service and recent throttle actuator replacements. The hydraulic steering rack offers the tactile feedback modern EPS systems lack. Cosmetically, the Alpine White finish over Novillo leather is well-preserved, showing only minor signs of use consistent with a well-loved driver\u2019s car. A mechanically sound example for the purist seeking an analog experience.",
